& [LambdaMellinBridgeUnit] is a project-local finite diagnostic contract
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is 7783707d-15da-4d52-a206-f66b034bf71d
  + [manifest_uuid] is 55f2fc43-3523-4e21-b170-1f50a15c5278
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is d24549d0-1b26-49d0-89c2-5ce79b735db9
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is test whether a shared weighted Lambda contribution unit can compare explicit-formula residual rails with Euler-product/log-derivative cutoff rails without collapsing identity
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, RH evidence, independent zero certification, critical-line authority, universal scale-law ranking, or explicit/Euler identity fusion

  = must: work only with Re(s) > 1 samples
  = must: use the finite von Mangoldt/psi relation as the shared unit, not raw residual magnitude
  = must: compute exact finite Lambda sum Sum_{n<=N} Lambda(n)n^-s as the local Euler/log-derivative cutoff rail
  = must: compute explicit-formula psi estimates psi_hat(n) for n <= N using declared scale law, multiplier, and zero-height window
  = must: derive explicit-side finite Lambda-like increments by psi_hat(n) - psi_hat(n-1)
  = must: compare explicit-weighted sum Sum_{n<=N}(psi_hat(n)-psi_hat(n-1))n^-s against the exact finite Lambda sum over the same N and s
  = must: also report exact finite Lambda sum residual against -zeta_prime/zeta(s) so the tail-to-infinity remains visible
  = must: report bridge residual, exact cutoff residual, combined explicit-to-infinite residual, and normalized ratios
  = must: include sample-level rows for N, s, scale law, multiplier, window, explicit finite sum, exact finite sum, and residual magnitudes
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_lambda_mellin_bridge_not_rh_evidence
  = must: treat mpmath zetazero and zeta derivative evaluation as numerical library lookup, not proof authority
  - never: compare x-domain and s-domain residuals as if they share units without this projection
  - never: infer RH proof, disproof, zero certification, or critical-line truth from finite bridge traces
  - never: collapse explicit-zero truncation identity into Euler prime-power cutoff identity

& [DefaultBridgeGrid] is the bounded comparison grid
  + [n_bounds] is 50, 100, and 200
  + [samples] is s=2+0i, s=2+14.134725141734693790457251983562i, and s=1.5+14.134725141734693790457251983562i
  + [scale_law] is log
  + [multipliers] is 16 and 32
  + [windows] is sharp, fejer, lanczos, and hann
  + [rationale] is keep the explicit-side finite-difference grid small enough for deterministic local computation while testing whether the shared unit is coherent

